{"data":{"actions":[{"callId":"chatcmpl-tool-b245432c64e8ac98","input":{"filename":"product_feedback_action_report.md","title":"Product Feedback Synthesizer – Prioritized Action Report","markdown":"# Prioritized Action Report (Product Feedback Synthesizer)\n\n**Scope**: Synthesize recent feedback records, assess severity, and recommend roadmap actions. All conclusions are based on the latest local record analysis (3 records, total risk score 19, opportunity 10.8).\n\n---\n\n## 1. Summary of Findings\n| Record ID | Title | Status | Impact | Risk Score | Opportunity Score | Key Insight |\n|-----------|-------|--------|--------|------------|-------------------|-------------|\n| **34‑A** | Product feedback synthesizer priority case | **Urgent** | 52,778 | **6** (risk 10) | 7 | Highest‑impact open item; clusters feedback, needs immediate action. |\n| **34‑C** | Blocked follow‑up | **Blocked** | 25,174 | **5** (risk 7) | 2.5 | Requires cross‑functional coordination before moving forward. |\n| **34‑B** | Routine queue item | **In Review** | 12,842 | **2** (risk 2) | 1.3 | Lower‑risk operational item; useful for benchmarking. |\n\n**Aggregate Scores**: Total risk = 19, total opportunity = 10.8. The distribution indicates a skew toward high‑risk items that demand attention.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Prioritization Framework\n1. **Severity (Risk)** – Primary driver; higher risk → higher priority.  \n2. **Impact** – Financial/strategic impact multiplies urgency.  \n3. **Status** – Blocked items are deferred until dependencies are cleared.  \n4. **Opportunity** – Secondary factor; high‑opportunity items may be fast‑track for quick wins.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Recommended Actions (by priority)\n\n### 📌 **High Priority – Immediate Execution**\n**Record 34‑A – Urgent, High Risk**\n- **Action**: Deploy a focused sprint to enhance clustering algorithms and integrate severity tagging.\n- **Rationale**: Largest impact (≈$53k) and top risk score; delays degrade feedback loop quality.\n- **Assumptions**: Existing data pipelines can support the refined model with minor engineering effort.\n- **Next Steps**:\n  1. Assign a product owner and create a JIRA epic.\n  2. Allocate 2 engineers (ML & backend) for a 2‑week spike.\n  3. Define success metrics (accuracy > 85 %, latency < 200 ms).\n\n### ⏳ **Medium Priority – Unblock & Align**\n**Record 34‑C – Blocked, Moderate Risk**\n- **Action**: Initiate cross‑functional coordination (Design, Legal, Compliance) to resolve blocking dependencies.\n- **Rationale**: Substantial impact (≈$25k) but cannot proceed until blockers cleared.\n- **Assumptions**: Dependencies are primarily policy reviews; meetings can be scheduled within 1 week.\n- **Next Steps**:\n  1. Hold a coordination call with stakeholders.\n  2. Document required approvals and create a dependency tracker.\n  3. Once cleared, treat as a **High Priority** item (similar scope to 34‑A).\n\n### ✅ **Low Priority – Routine Maintenance**\n**Record 34‑B – In Review, Low Risk**\n- **Action**: Incorporate as part of regular backlog grooming; schedule after higher‑risk items.\n- **Rationale**: Minor impact and risk; serves as a benchmark for future improvements.\n- **Assumptions**: No immediate resource constraints; can be bundled with other low‑effort tickets.\n- **Next Steps**:\n  1. Add to the next sprint’s “maintenance” bucket.\n  2. Track execution metrics for continuous improvement.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Risks & Mitigations\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| **Resource overload** – Focusing on 34‑A may stretch team capacity. | Stagger effort: start 34‑A, parallel unblock 34‑C via a dedicated liaison. |\n| **Blocking dependencies** – 34‑C may stall longer than anticipated. | Escalate to senior leadership after 5 business days without resolution. |\n| **Model regression** – New clustering may degrade existing performance. | Implement A/B testing and rollback plan before full rollout.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Open Questions & Assumptions\n- **Data Availability**: Assumed current feedback datasets are clean and accessible. Verify data quality before model work.\n- **Stakeholder Buy‑in**: Assumes product leadership agrees on the risk‑first prioritization; confirm alignment.\n- **Timeline Accuracy**: Estimated 2‑week spike for 34‑A based on historic velocity; may vary.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Immediate Next Steps (Actionable Checklist)\n- [ ] Create JIRA epic for **34‑A** and assign owners.\n- [ ] Schedule cross‑functional sync for **34‑C** blockers.\n- [ ] Add **34‑B** to next sprint backlog.\n- [ ] Review data pipeline health; confirm readiness for clustering enhancements.\n\n*Prepared by the Product Feedback Synthesizer (Agent 34). All recommendations are grounded in the latest local record analysis (risk = 19, opportunity = 10.8).*\n"},"kind":"tool-call","toolName":"write_report"}],"sequence":0,"stepIndex":3,"turnId":"turn_0"},"type":"actions.requested","meta":{"at":"2026-06-18T15:21:32.151Z"}}
